# ───────── data/ ─────────
# Dynamic data (memory/, skills/, evolution/, runs/) lives in the sibling repo
# ../AgenticSTS-Data (see CLAUDE.md § "Data Repository Split"). Only these
# static / per-machine paths stay under data/ in the main repo:
#   data/knowledge/                    — game knowledge DB, upstream-synced
#   data/patches/                      — authored patch manifests
#   data/version_compatibility.json    — authored
#   data/reports/                      — local audit output

# Ignore the sibling-owned subtrees if they get accidentally recreated locally.
data/memory/
data/skills/
data/evolution/
data/runs/

# Per-machine operational state — never in sibling, never committed.
data/batch_pending.json
data/skill_discovery_counter.json
data/benchmark/
data/eval/
data/hidden_gem_ab_results.json
data/.postrun.lock

# Patch-pipeline snapshots — write-once, never commit
data.snapshots/

# ───────── logs/ ─────────
# Per-run JSONL session logs. Multi-GB, not useful to share raw.
logs/

# ───────── scratch / build / reflection ─────────
out/
scratch/
_reflect_sts2/
.tmp_test/
tests/_tmp_session_logger/
tools/**/bin/
tools/**/obj/
/*.png

# ───────── C# mod ─────────
# The C# mod lives in the sibling repo ShandaAI/AgenticSTS:AgenticSTS-Mod (../AgenticSTS-Mod/),
# split from STS2-Agent-Fork/ on 2026-04-29. Build outputs are ignored in that
# sibling repo's own .gitignore — nothing to ignore here.

# ───────── frontend build output ─────────
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.vite/

# ───────── GDRE auto-regenerated log ─────────
# Rewrites a meaningless extraction-time line on every run; pure churn.
data/knowledge/gdre_export.log

# ───────── Locally-regenerated game content (NOT redistributed) ─────────
# Verbatim / derived game strings — AGPL-3.0 upstream or extracted from the
# proprietary game package. Regenerate with scripts.sync_upstream_data /
# scripts.extract_pck_localization. See data/knowledge/README.md.
data/knowledge/upstream/
data/knowledge/*_dll.json
data/knowledge/afflictions.json
data/knowledge/powers.json
data/knowledge/localization/

# ───────── Runtime locks ─────────
*.postrun.lock
.postrun.lock

# ───────── paper/ ─────────
# Cloned competitor repos for comparative analysis (paper/competitors/).
# External repositories — cite via GitHub URLs and document findings in
# paper/narrative/competitor_analysis.md. Do not commit their contents.
paper/competitors/
paper/reference_papers/
